## stacklite — skill routing

When the user's request matches an available command, invoke it as your FIRST action.
The command has specialized workflows that produce better results than ad-hoc answers.

Routing rules:
- Product ideas, "is this worth building", brainstorming → `/sl-plan`
- Architecture review, "lock in the plan" → `/sl-eng-review`
- Code review, "check my diff", pre-landing review → `/sl-review`
- Security audit, "check for vulnerabilities" → `/sl-secure`
- Performance review, "check for perf issues" → `/sl-perf`
- Ship, deploy, push, create PR → `/sl-ship`
- Bugs, errors, "why is this broken" → `/sl-investigate`
- Weekly retro, "what did we ship" → `/sl-retro`
- Update docs after shipping → `/sl-doc`
